one_reviews_text: Cool to learn and experience these shapes and patterns. Would love a way to make more interactive somehow, but very cool

May only interest people who already know a bit what sacred geometry is... Very interesting to manipulate 3D objects to get a better 3D representation of the shapes, and also about Pi and Phi ratios. Liked the video too (made me think about Nassim Haramein's theory), and "El Castillo". Thanks to the developer for sharing it, knowing probably that so few people would be interested !

I would give it a ten if the designer could make it work on Windows Mixed Reality. For now I can only walk around the area but can't interact with the objects. I think a puzzle game that requires knowledge of these geometric concepts would be amazing. I hope you incorporate it eventually.
